captions.text: Today we're going to Geocat.
It's a cat cafe!
It's just filled with cats!
And you just hold them!
And you pet them!
And you snuggle them and you love them!
Let's go!
[music]
Now, there are some rules when it comes to cat club.
Rule number one is YOU DO NOT TALK ABOUT CAT CLUB
I want you to hit me as hard as you can
Simon...I, think those are the wrong rules.
Ok, no, seriously. Here are the real rules.
First thing's first, entrance to Giocat is 8000 won per person.
That will give you a free drink.
When you are done with your drink, DO NOT GIVE THE STRAW TO THE KITTIES!
Straws and Kitties are a bad, bad combination,
and may result in the end of the world.
Rule number two is not to scare the cats.
Seriously! They're so cute! Why would you want to scare them?
That's just sick!
Rule number three is to turn off your flash.
Kitties don't like to be papparazzid.
It hurts their kitty eyes, and you don't want to hurt a kitty.
Rule number four not sure why this is listed as a rule, but supposedly people squish kitties.
So don't be one of them!
If you see a kitty on its back, don't be tempted to squish it.
Rule number five is to pet the kitties only if they want to be petted.
See a kitty in your lap? It's ok to pet it.
See a kitty running away from you? It's not okay to pet it.
Rule number six is not to pick up the kitties.
This includes not picking up kitties half way and making them dance
the way we make Spudgy dance. Dogs can handle the dancing.
Kitties can't.
Rule number seven is not to wake a sleeping kitty.
Ever hear the saying "let sleeping dogs lie?"
The same applies to cats.
Rule number eight is not to give fast food to the cats.
I'm not sure why you'd be bringing fries to a cat cafe to begin with,
but, if you ever feel like sharing a whopper with a cat, think twice.
Rule number nine is obvious. DON'T PULL CAT TAILS! Just don't do it!
The cats will not only squish up their faces the way this one is squishing up its face,
but it also might maul you! And you'll deserve it!
Pulling a cat's tail like that! Shame on you!
[cute cat music]
Oh, hi Spudgy.
[angry dog music]
I hope you don't see this.
undefined
